memberdef.name: PATH
memberdef.initializer: = required(500, "manifest_path", Types.StringType.get(), "Location URI with FS scheme")

memberdef.name: LENGTH
memberdef.initializer: = required(501, "manifest_length", Types.LongType.get(), "Total file size in bytes")

memberdef.name: SPEC_ID
memberdef.initializer: = required(502, "partition_spec_id", Types.IntegerType.get(), "Spec ID used to write")

memberdef.name: SEQUENCE_NUMBER
memberdef.initializer: = optional( 515, "sequence_number", Types.LongType.get(), "Sequence number when the manifest was added")

memberdef.name: MIN_SEQUENCE_NUMBER
memberdef.initializer: = optional( 516, "min_sequence_number", Types.LongType.get(), "Lowest sequence number in the manifest")

memberdef.name: SNAPSHOT_ID
memberdef.initializer: = optional( 503, "added_snapshot_id", Types.LongType.get(), "Snapshot ID that added the manifest")

memberdef.name: PARTITION_SUMMARY_TYPE
memberdef.initializer: = Types.StructType.of( required( 509, "contains_null", Types.BooleanType.get(), "True if any file has a null partition value"), optional( 518, "contains_nan", Types.BooleanType.get(), "True if any file has a nan partition value"), optional( 510, "lower_bound", Types.BinaryType.get(), "Partition lower bound for all files"), optional( 511, "upper_bound", Types.BinaryType.get(), "Partition upper bound for all files"))

memberdef.name: PARTITION_SUMMARIES
memberdef.initializer: = optional( 507, "partitions", Types.ListType.ofRequired(508, PARTITION_SUMMARY_TYPE), "Summary for each partition")

memberdef.name: SCHEMA
memberdef.initializer: = new Schema( PATH, LENGTH, SPEC_ID, MANIFEST_CONTENT, SEQUENCE_NUMBER, MIN_SEQUENCE_NUMBER, SNAPSHOT_ID, ADDED_FILES_COUNT, EXISTING_FILES_COUNT, DELETED_FILES_COUNT, ADDED_ROWS_COUNT, EXISTING_ROWS_COUNT, DELETED_ROWS_COUNT, PARTITION_SUMMARIES, KEY_METADATA)

detaileddescription.para: Returns fully qualified path to the file, suitable for constructing a Hadoop Path.
Returns length of the manifest file.
Returns iD of the PartitionSpec used to write the manifest file.
Returns the content stored in the manifest; either DATA or DELETES.
Returns the sequence number of the commit that added the manifest file.
Returns the lowest data sequence number of any live file in the manifest.
Returns iD of the snapshot that added the manifest file to table metadata.
Returns true if the manifest contains ADDED entries or if the count is not known.

simplesect.para: whether this manifest contains entries with ADDED status

detaileddescription.para: Returns the number of files with status ADDED in the manifest file.
Returns the total number of rows in all files with status ADDED in the manifest file.
Returns true if the manifest contains EXISTING entries or if the count is not known.

simplesect.para: whether this manifest contains entries with EXISTING status

detaileddescription.para: Returns the number of files with status EXISTING in the manifest file.
Returns the total number of rows in all files with status EXISTING in the manifest file.
Returns true if the manifest contains DELETED entries or if the count is not known.

simplesect.para: whether this manifest contains entries with DELETED status

detaileddescription.para: Returns the number of files with status DELETED in the manifest file.
Returns the total number of rows in all files with status DELETED in the manifest file.
Returns a list of partition field summaries.

Each summary corresponds to a field in the manifest file's partition spec, by ordinal. For example, the partition spec [ ts_day=date(ts), type=identity(type) ] will have 2 summaries. The first summary is for the ts_day partition field and the second is for the type partition field.

simplesect.para: a list of partition field summaries, one for each field in the manifest's spec

detaileddescription.para: Returns metadata about how this manifest file is encrypted, or null if the file is stored in plain text.
Copies this manifest file. Readers can reuse manifest file instances; use this method to make defensive copies.

simplesect.para: a copy of this manifest file

detaileddescription.para: Represents a manifest file that can be scanned to find files in a table.
